detail_description: When exploring Manaus, a visit to the Mercado Municipal Adolpho Lisboa is an absolute must. This vibrant market, inspired by the original Les Halles in Paris, serves as a lively gathering spot for both locals and tourists. Here, you can indulge in unique Amazonian delicacies while browsing through an array of fresh produce, exotic meats, fish, tropical fruits, and colorful handicrafts that make perfect souvenirs.
name: Mercado Municipal Adolpho Lisboa
address: R. dos Barés, 46 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69009-365, Brazil

excerpt: Famed Renaissance theater built in 1896 during the city's rubber boom & hosting concerts & tours.
detail_description: The Amazon Theatre, a renowned Renaissance theater constructed during Manaus's rubber boom in 1896, is a stunning landmark influenced by European design and materials. The opulent venue hosts various events, including an opera festival in April and May. Visitors can take guided tours to admire the theater's grand construction. Situated at Largo de Sao Sebastiao, it is surrounded by attractions like the central church and a lively square for a complete experience of Manaus's charm.
name: Teatro Amazonas
address: Largo de São Sebastião - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69067-080, Brazil

excerpt: Natural attraction where dark- & sandy-colored rivers meet & parallel each other without mixing.
detail_description: The Meeting of Waters, locally known as Encuetro de los Aguas, is a must-see natural attraction near Manaus. Here, the dark Rio Negro and the milky Rio Solimoes come together to form the Amazon River. The distinct colors of these rivers run alongside each other for nearly a mile without mixing due to differences in temperature, density, and velocity. This phenomenon creates a stunning spectacle that attracts many travelers.
name: Meeting of Waters
address: Careiro da Várzea - State of Amazonas, 69255-000, Brazil

excerpt: Restored 19th-century rubber baron's estate featuring period decor, history exhibits & gardens.
detail_description: Palácio Rio Negro is a beautifully restored 19th-century estate located in the historic center of Manaus. Once the residence of Waldemar Scholz, a prominent German rubber baron, it has served various purposes over the years, including as the Amazonas state capital and a private home. Since 1997, it has been transformed into a cultural center hosting art exhibitions and musical concerts. Visitors can also explore its gardens and learn about its rich history through exhibits.
name: Palácio Rio Negro
address: Av. Sete de Setembro, 1546 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69005-141, Brazil

excerpt: Manaus, on the banks of the Negro River in northwestern Brazil, is the capital of the vast state of Amazonas. It's a major departure point for the surrounding Amazon Rainforest. Just east of the city, the dark Negro River converges with the brown, muddy Solimões River resulting in a striking visual phenomenon called the “Meeting of the Waters.” The combined tributaries form the Amazon River.
detail_description: Manaus, situated on the banks of the Negro River in northwestern Brazil, serves as the capital of Amazonas state and a key gateway to the surrounding Amazon Rainforest. A notable natural wonder near the city is the 'Meeting of the Waters,' where the dark Negro River meets with the muddy Solimões River to form the Amazon River.
name: Manaus
address: State of Amazonas, Brazil

excerpt: Trees & historical buildings surround this major plaza featuring a grand monument & performances.
detail_description: Largo de São Sebastião, also known as São Sebastião Square, is a major plaza in Manaus that boasts a mix of European and Middle-Eastern architectural styles. The square is surrounded by historical buildings and trees, with a grand monument at its center. It has become a focal point for visitors, offering pavement bars and cafes, as well as hosting live musical and cultural events.
name: Largo de São Sebastião
address: Rua 10 de Julho - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-060, Brazil

detail_description: Restaurante Caxiri Manaus is a renowned culinary icon in the heart of Manaus, housed in a beautifully restored mansion with expansive windows overlooking the majestic Teatro Amazonas. Led by acclaimed chef Debora Shornik, known for her expertise in Amazonian cuisine, this establishment offers an elegant yet relaxed dining experience. The menu features gourmet interpretations of traditional Amazon dishes, such as tambaqui river fish, and creatively crafted cocktails infused with local flavors.
name: Restaurante Caxiri Manaus
address: Rua 10 de Julho, 495 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-000, Brazil

excerpt: 19th-century former police headquarters housing museums of art, numismatics, archaeology & more.
detail_description: Nestled at the intersection of Avenida Sete de Setembro and historic streets, the Palacete Provincial stands as a remarkable 19th-century former police headquarters that now houses an impressive array of five museums. This cultural gem showcases diverse collections ranging from art to numismatics and archaeology, offering visitors a glimpse into the rich heritage of the region.
name: Palacete Provincial
address: Praça Heliodoro Balbi, S/N - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69005-260, Brazil

excerpt: Forested area with guided tours of native Amazonian flora, fauna & culture, plus a viewing tower.
detail_description: Museu da Amazônia, also known as MUSA, is located within the Adolpho Ducke Forest Reserve, a 100-hectare native forest owned by the National Institute for Amazonia Research. The museum offers guided tours showcasing the diverse flora, fauna, and culture of the Amazon. Visitors can explore outdoor exhibits featuring aquariums, snake and butterfly labs, an orchid house, and displays on native species.
name: Museu da Amazônia - MUSA
address: Av. Margarita, 6305 - Cidade de Deus, Manaus - AM, 69099-415, Brazil

excerpt: Large urban park along a stream, with an iron portico of arches, a trellised walkway & monuments.
detail_description: Parque Senador Jefferson Péres is a well-maintained urban park located in the heart of the city. It features lush greenery, walking and biking tracks, and a casual laid-back ambiance. The park offers a quiet and beautiful setting for morning or afternoon walks, with plenty of benches and exercise equipment available. Despite being close to the busy city center, it provides a relaxing atmosphere away from the noise.
name: Parque Senador Jefferson Péres
address: Av. Lourenço da Silva Braga, 1507 - Centro, Manaus - AM, Brazil

excerpt: Scenic conservation area featuring forested trails, play equipment, an amphitheater & a library.
detail_description: Parque Municipal do Mindu, established in the late 1980s, was created to protect the natural habitat of the endangered Manaus Sagui-de-Manaus primate species. This lush forested park offers a serene escape from city life, with opportunities for hiking, birdwatching, and connecting with nature. Despite some pollution concerns, it's a great spot for walking and enjoying the calming sounds of the river.
name: Parque Municipal do Mindu
address: R. Domingos José Martins, S/n - Parque Dez de Novembro, Manaus - AM, 69098-257, Brazil

detail_description: Restaurante Banzeiro in Manaus offers a unique dining experience with its exotic decor featuring vibrant photos and a canoe symbolizing the movement of boats on the river. The grill uses fire and embers, incorporating ancestral techniques from the northwest Amazon. Classic dishes like fish, shrimp, and meat are elevated with new textures and ingredients that evoke the flavors of the forest. Chef Felipe Schaedler transforms Amazonian bounty into surprising fare, such as crunchy tambaqui ribs.
name: Restaurante Banzeiro Manaus
address: R. Libertador, 102 - Nossa Sra. das Graças, Manaus - AM, 69057-070, Brazil

detail_description: Abaré SUP and FOOD is a unique floating restaurant on the Rio Negro that offers an innovative menu featuring detox juices and exotic tapioca pancakes. Diners can enjoy complimentary stand-up paddleboarding while taking in the stunning sunset views and lively atmosphere with good tunes at the bar. For a more relaxed experience, visitors can opt for a morning coffee to avoid the crowds and strong sun rays.
name: Abaré SUP and FOOD
address: Rm, Estr. Iate Clube - Tarumã, Manaus - AM, 69037-295, Brazil

detail_description: Paróquia de São Sebastião, located in Manaus, has undergone a complete renovation to commemorate the 100th anniversary of the Capuchin Franciscan order's arrival. Despite not being the largest or oldest church in Manaus, it is renowned for its stunning interior and beautiful artwork. The church features magnificent paintings, including some from Italy, and a life-size nativity scene. Its serene atmosphere and well-maintained architecture make it a popular attraction for visitors seeking tranquility.
name: Paróquia de São Sebastião
address: Rua 10 de Julho, S/N - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-060, Brazil

detail_description: The restaurant Biatuwi - Casa de Comida Indígena Manaus is a great choice for people looking for an authentic, natural and high-quality meal. The refinement of the details without losing the authenticity of the secular forest is impressive. The meal felt like it was from the 19th century, which is a testament to the quality of this restaurant.
name: Biatuwi - Casa de Comida Indígena Manaus
address: R. Bernardo Ramos, 97 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69005-360, Brazil

detail_description: The Centro Cultural dos Povos da Amazônia in Manaus is a vibrant celebration of the diverse cultures found within the Amazon Basin. This cultural center offers a rich exploration of indigenous tribes through exhibits showcasing their customs, art, and history. Visitors can also experience lively cultural events held at the venue, adding to the dynamic atmosphere. The complex houses a museum with artifacts from various indigenous groups, a film-screening room, and an arena for festivals and events.
name: Centro Cultural dos Povos da Amazônia
address: Distrito Industrial I, Av. Silves, 2222 - Crespo, Manaus - AM, 69073-270, Brazil

detail_description: Ponte Rio Negro, also known as the Rio Negro Bridge, is a cable-stayed bridge built in 2010 to replace the slow ferry service to Iranduba and its surroundings. The 2.2-mile-long steel bridge has significantly reduced travel time and improved access to the untouched rainforest beyond. It allows shipping traffic on the Amazon River to pass freely.
name: Ponte Rio Negro (Jorn. Phelippe Daou)
address: Pte. Jorn. Phelippe Daou, Manaus - AM, Brazil

excerpt: Lively Centro spreads around the 1896 Amazon Theatre, an ornate, Renaissance-style venue on Largo de São Sebastião, a tree-lined square with a decorative cobblestone pavement. Museums in the area cover local history, native culture, and art, and Amazon cruises depart from the busy Port of Manaus. Eateries include spots for barbecued meats and grilled freshwater fish, while simple bars serve cold beer and snacks.
detail_description: Centro is a vibrant area surrounding the 1896 Amazon Theatre, an elaborate Renaissance-style building located on Largo de São Sebastião. The square features a charming cobblestone pavement and is lined with trees. Visitors can explore museums showcasing local history, indigenous culture, and art. Additionally, the bustling Port of Manaus serves as a departure point for Amazon cruises.
name: Centro
address: Manaus - State of Amazonas, Brazil

detail_description: Monumento à Abertura dos Portos às Nações Amigas is a striking monument located in a bustling square. It replaced an earlier column and was opened in 1900 to commemorate the opening of the Amazon River ports by D. Pedro II in 1866. The sculptural group, designed by Domenico de Angelis and created in Rome by Enrico Quatrini, is a popular spot for locals and tourists to relax and take photos.
name: Monumento à Abertura dos Portos às Nações Amigas.
address: Rua 10 de Julho - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-060, Brazil

detail_description: Arena da Amazônia, situated in the heart of Manaus, was a key venue for the 2014 World Cup in Brazil. Originally built in 1970, it underwent a transformation to become a modern stadium with sustainable features like rainwater harvesting and solar energy utilization. Despite concerns about its long-term viability due to the local club's modest attendance, the arena can accommodate over 40,000 fans.
name: Arena da Amazônia
address: Av. Constantino Nery, 5001 - Flores, Manaus - AM, 69058-795, Brazil

excerpt: This remote white-sand beach features swimming, boating & picnic tables with umbrellas.
detail_description: Moon Beach, also known as Praia da Lua, is a remote white-sand beach located 23 miles off the coast of Manaus. It has been elected as the best beach in Manaus by Lonely Planet and is named for its crescent moon shape formed over the Black River. Accessible only by water, it offers swimming, boating, and picnic tables with umbrellas. The sand strip may not exist at low tide but is a sight to behold during high tide.
name: Moon Beach
address: Manaus - State of Amazonas, Brazil

detail_description: Galeria do Largo is a must-visit for art enthusiasts. The gallery features a rotating collection of top-notch sculptures and paintings by both emerging and renowned artists, ensuring a fresh experience with every visit. After exploring the art, visitors can unwind at the attached cafe, indulging in delectable muffins, Pastel de Melem, and comforting coffee. Additionally, the gallery hosts permanent exhibitions and installations by local artists, often showcasing works that have gained international acclaim.
name: Galeria do Largo
address: R. Costa Azevedo, 290 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-230, Brazil

detail_description: Centro Cultural Usina Chaminé is a remarkable destination that beautifully marries innovative architecture with cultural experiences. Originally designed as a sewage treatment plant, this unique venue has been transformed into a sensory museum that invites visitors to engage all five senses. With its commitment to enhancing the visitor experience, Centro Cultural Usina Chaminé stands out as an enchanting place worth exploring.
name: Centro Cultural Usina Chaminé
address: Av. Lourenço da Silva Braga, s/n - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69005-015, Brazil

excerpt: Museum in a neoclassical palace featuring hands-on exhibits tracing the culture & history of Manaus.
detail_description: The Museu da Cidade de Manaus (Paço da Liberdade) is a Brazilian museum located in the heart of Manaus, offering an immersive experience into the rich history and culture of the region. Housed in a neoclassical palace, it features interactive exhibits that trace the diverse backgrounds and traditions of the people of Manaus. Visitors can explore displays on indigenous cultures, art, natural history, and more.
name: Museu da Cidade de Manaus - MUMA (Paço da Liberdade)
address: R. Gabriel Salgado - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69005-340, Brazil

excerpt: Busy harbor on the Amazon River filled with cargo & cruise ships, colorful vendors & food stalls.
detail_description: The Port of Manaus, situated on the Amazon River, is a bustling harbor filled with cargo and cruise ships, as well as vibrant vendors and food stalls. It is strategically located between Sao Vicente beach and the Adolpho Lisboa Municipal Market, providing convenient access to customs facilities, warehouses, and container ramps. This important port serves the northern region of Brazil, covering almost the entire state of Amazonas along with parts of Roraima and Rondonia.
name: Port of Manaus
address: R. Taqueirinha, 25 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69005-420, Brazil

name: Arquipélago das Anavilhanas Turismo
address: Av. Ramos Ferreira, 922 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-425, Brazil

excerpt: Understated hotel in a chic mansion with a restaurant & a bar, plus an outdoor pool & a gym.
detail_description: The Hotel Villa Amazônia is a boutique hotel located in the heart of Manaus, in an elegant mansion from the golden rubber age. Offering luxurious suites with views of a natural pool and indoor garden, as well as delicious cuisine from the Fitz Carraldo bistro, this is one of the best places to stay in Manaus.
name: Hotel Villa Amazônia
address: Rua 10 de Julho, 315 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-060, Brazil

excerpt: Upmarket hotel set in historic mansions & offering a chic restaurant, plus a bar & a rooftop pool.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Manaus, Juma Ópera Hotel is a stunning blend of historical elegance and contemporary luxury. This boutique hotel, housed in a beautifully restored mansion from the rubber boom era, offers guests an unforgettable experience just steps away from the iconic Amazonas Theatre. With 41 spacious suites adorned with tasteful decor, visitors can unwind by the rooftop pool while enjoying breathtaking views of the theater.
name: Juma Ópera Hotel
address: Rua 10 de Julho, 481 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-060, Brazil

detail_description: Tambaqui de Banda is a renowned restaurant located in the heart of Manaus, known for its authentic regional dishes and, most notably, its signature dish - the Tambaqui de Banda. The menu offers a variety of options including desserts, salads, and snacks. A highlight is their special house-made pepper sauce that receives high praise from visitors.
name: Tambaqui de Banda
address: R. José Clemente, 596 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-070, Brazil

detail_description: O Lenhador is a popular Amazonian restaurant located in Manaus, known for its exotic turtle dishes and traditional regional cuisine. The restaurant offers a buffet with a focus on fish and seafood recipes, as well as hearty portions of regional meats. Its rustic atmosphere and colorful decorations create a cozy dining experience, while the leafy garden outside adds to the ambiance. Visitors can enjoy dishes such as turtle, alligator, stingray, and lamb, with the option to pay extra for specific items.
name: Restaurante O Lenhador
address: Av. do Turismo, 2371 - Ponta Negra, Manaus - AM, 69041-010, Brazil

detail_description: Tacacá da Gisela is more than just a typical street stall; it's a permanent fixture in the square across from Teatro Amazonas. The ornate green columns and tiled roof make it stand out. Both locals and tourists frequent this spot for its signature dish, tacaca, a tangy broth that surprises even the most seasoned palates.
name: Tacacá da Gisela
address: R. José Clemente - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-070, Brazil

detail_description: Restaurante Moquém do Banzeiro is a casual dining spot in Manaus that focuses on serving local fish cooked over live embers, known as "moquem" style. The restaurant opened its doors in 2016 and has gained a reputation for offering delicious Amazonian cuisine. Diners rave about the must-try Sweet and Sour Tambaqui Ribs and the perfectly salted Grilled Tambaqui.
name: Restaurante Moquém do Banzeiro
address: Av. Umberto Calderaro, 455 - Adrianópolis, Manaus - AM, 69057-002, Brazil

excerpt: Contemporary property offering a restaurant & a piano bar, plus a rooftop pool & a sauna.
detail_description: Nestled within the vibrant Millennium Center Complex, Manaus Hotéis Millennium is a contemporary haven that combines comfort and convenience. This hotel boasts an array of amenities including a rooftop pool with stunning views, a sauna, and a well-equipped fitness center. Guests can enjoy delicious meals at the on-site restaurant or unwind at the piano bar after a day of exploring. The spacious apartments come complete with balconies, air conditioning, kitchen facilities, and satellite TV for your entertainment.
name: Manaus Hotéis Millennium
address: Av. Djalma Batista, 1661 - Chapada, Manaus - AM, 69050-970, Brazil

excerpt: Colorful dorms & rooms in a hip hostel offering complimentary Wi-Fi & a shared kitchen, plus a bar.
detail_description: Hostel Manaus is a vibrant and trendy hostel located in the heart of Manaus. It offers colorful dorms and rooms with complimentary Wi-Fi, a shared kitchen, and a bar. The hostel provides convenient amenities such as concierge services, a communal living room, and air-conditioned guestrooms. Its unique location in the downtown area allows easy access to popular attractions like the Museum of the Northern Man, Palacio Rio Negro, historical markets, and the Teatro Amazonas (Opera House).
name: Hostel Manaus
address: R. Dona Libânia, 215 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-250, Brazil

excerpt: Pared-back rooms in a straightforward hotel offering afternoon tea & complimentary Wi-Fi.
detail_description: Seringal Hotel, located in Manaus, is a great place to stay if you're looking for a straightforward hotel with afternoon tea and complimentary Wi-Fi. The rooms are spacious, comfortable and include all the modern amenities you could wish for. The location is excellent too - within walking distance of the famous Amazon Theatre.
name: Seringal Hotel
address: R. Monsenhor Coutinho, 758 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69020-230, Brazil

excerpt: Multilevel indoor shopping mall featuring stores, a food court & entertainment, including a cinema.
detail_description: Located in Manaus, Amazonas Shopping Center is a multilevel indoor mall that offers a wide range of stores, a food court, and entertainment options such as a cinema. The mall is part of the city's array of shopping centers and is known for its typical Brazilian chain shops, restaurants, supermarkets, clothing stores, banks, and pharmacies. It serves as a popular meeting point for locals seeking refuge from the humid weather outside.
name: Amazonas Shopping Center
address: Av. Djalma Batista, 482 - Parque 10 de Novembro, Manaus - AM, 69050-010, Brazil

detail_description: This small hotel is situated close to the Church of Nossa Senhora da Conceicao and offers views of the city. The staff are friendly and helpful, making it a great place to stay in Manaus.
name: MURAL LIVING LOCAÇÕES E HOTELARIA
address: R. Dr. Moreira, 168 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69005-250, Brazil

excerpt: Scenic coastal destination known for its wide sand beach, sunset views, park & eateries.
detail_description: Ponta Negra Beach is a picturesque coastal destination with a wide sandy beach, stunning sunset views, and a variety of parks and eateries. Visitors can explore the city through guided tours that include the charming Ponta Negra boardwalk, the bustling city market offering regional products, and the iconic Teatro Amazonas. The beach is popular among sightseers for swimming and immersing in local culture.
name: Ponta Negra Beach
address: Manaus - State of Amazonas, Brazil

name: Zoológico Do CIGS - São Jorge
address: São Jorge, Manaus - AM, Brazil

name: Seringal Museum
address: Igarapé São João - Afluente do Igarapé do Tarumã, Mirim, Manaus - AM, Brazil

name: Parque Ecologico Janauari
address: 6900000, Iranduba - AM, 69405-000, Brazil

detail_description: Hotel Tropical Zoo is a 5-star, 600+-room hotel with immaculate rooms and excellent dining. It offers a range of amenities including its own zoo, tour boat, nightclubs, and pools. The hotel also provides guided tours to nearby attractions such as Adolpho Ducke's Botanical Garden, the Tropical Zoo, and the Natural History Museum which offer insights into the biodiversity of Amazonia.
name: Hotel Tropical Zoo
address: Av. Coronel Teixeira, 1320 - Ponta Negra, Manaus - AM, 69030-480, Brazil

excerpt: Justice ministry in an elegant historic building offering guided tours & diverse cultural events.
detail_description: The Amazon Palace of Justice is an elegant historic building located across the road from the Opera House in the late 1800s. It serves as a cultural center offering guided tours and diverse events, making it a must-see for history enthusiasts interested in the old justice system of the Amazonas. The palace features tall corridors, chambers with varying temperatures, and a room that tells a macabre assassination story with a plot twist.
name: Amazon Palace of Justice
address: Av. Eduardo Ribeiro, 901 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69400-901, Brazil

detail_description: The Museu de Numismática Bernardo Ramos is located in the Provincial Palace in Manaus, on the historic Bernardo Ramos street. It houses an impressive collection of coins, medals, banknotes, decorations, stamps, and more from various places and time periods around the world. The museum's collection includes items such as the second smallest coin in the world and coins dating back to before Christ. Additionally, it features a small specialized library and over 35,000 pieces in total.
name: Museu de Numismática Bernardo Ramos
address: R. José Paranaguá - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69005-130, Brazil

detail_description: Museu da Casa Eduardo Ribeiro offers guided tours that shed light on the significance of Governor Eduardo Ribeiro for Manaus during his term from 1892 to 1896. The museum aims to uncover the historical truth about his Afro-descendant roots, as he was depicted with European physical features in paintings and photos. Despite some accessibility issues like a defective elevator, the museum is worth a visit with its free entry and informative guided tours.
name: Museu da Casa Eduardo Ribeiro
address: R. José Clemente, 322 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-070, Brazil

detail_description: GaleriAmazônica, established in 2008 in Manaus, is a unique store that aims to provide travelers and collectors with responsibly produced, high-quality products. Run by a respected Brazilian nonprofit organization and an indigenous community association, the gallery ensures that a percentage of sales directly benefits artisans in Amazonian communities. Visitors can expect to find original handmade items from various indigenous and traditional groups in the Amazon rainforest.
name: GaleriAmazônica
address: R. Costa Azevedo, 272 - Centro, Manaus - AM, 69010-230, Brazil

excerpt: Garden square on a former burial ground, featuring a memorial to poet Tenreiro Aranha & a pergola.
detail_description: Praça da Saudade is a garden square located in downtown Manaos, built on a former burial ground. It features a memorial to poet Tenreiro Aranha and a charming pergola. The park is popular among the city's youth, especially at night when pubs and informal snack shops are open. It also serves as a meeting place for LGBT and other alternative groups.
name: Praça da Saudade
address: R. Simão Bolívar - Centro, Manaus - AM, Brazil

detail_description: The Sambódromo de Manaus is a vibrant hub of celebration and culture, especially known for its lively festivals throughout the year. If you're planning a visit, consider timing your trip to coincide with the annual Jazz Festival in July or the Boi Manaus festival in October, which coincides with the city's birthday on October 24. These events feature an array of performances from local artists and tribal singers that truly showcase the region's rich musical heritage.
name: Sambódromo de Manaus
address: Av. Pedro Teixeira, 2565 - Flores, Manaus - AM, 69058-785, Brazil

name: Parque Ponte dos Bilhares
address: s/n, Av. Djalma Batista - Nossa Sra. das Gracas, AM, Brazil

excerpt: Park with paths amid a rainforest habitat dotted with statues of Amazonian fauna & mythical figures.
detail_description: Sumaúma State Park is a beautiful park filled with intertwining walkways within a lush tropical rainforest environment adorned with sculptures depicting the diverse wildlife of the Amazon region and mystical creatures. The park exudes an air of charm, showcasing its stunning surroundings and captivating statues. It offers visitors a captivating experience as they traverse through nature's beauty while admiring the various artistic representations that seamlessly blend into their natural setting.
name: Sumaúma State Park
address: Av. Bacuri, s/n - Nova Cidade, Manaus - AM, 69095-110, Brazil
